    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>3'2\" tall, even small for a gnome. Wild copper-red hair that defies gravity. Thick bushy amber eyebrows above sharp, fox-like amber eyes. A well-trimmed beard with two small braids tied with copper wire. A prominent gold tooth that glints when he grins. Wears a well-worn leather apron with an improbable number of pockets, all visibly stuffed.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Never forgets a face or a drink order. Collects rumors the way others collect coins. Speaks in elaborate metaphors when nervous. Makes every single customer feel like the most important person in the room.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>Keep The White Mouse prosperous and remain the most well-informed being in town. Genuinely enjoys helping adventurers.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Always polishes a glass when thinking — even a bone-dry clean one. Refers to himself in third person for solemn declarations ('Quick Thistledown does NOT betray his friends.'). Winks at nearly everyone.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Surprisingly warm, deep baritone for a gnome — guests often do a double-take. Carries a faint northern lilt. His laugh is loud, genuine, and utterly infectious.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> The White Mouse was bequeathed to him by his late mentor, Marta Plum, a halfling innkeeper of legendary warmth.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Information is the most valuable currency in the world. Everyone deserves a fair deal — but knowledge must be earned, not simply handed over.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> Cannot resist a truly juicy piece of gossip, even when sharing it puts him in danger. Hides a serious gambling problem.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Perfect entry NPC for new players — warm, approachable, packed with hooks. Sells rumors for 1 gp (may be unverified), confirmed info for 5 gp, sensitive intelligence for 10 gp + a favor. NOT a pushover: will use Suggestion or Charm Person without hesitation if cornered.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>Was a trained intelligence operative for the Silvermark Merchant Consortium. Knows the location of a hidden cache belonging to the deceased bandit lord 'Redclaw' Maren. Currently being blackmailed by an unknown party.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Marta Plum (deceased mentor) | 'Needle' Voss / Thieves' Guild (protection deal) | Lady Orvaine (dangerous patron) | Brother Stelwick (temple healer, trades potions for discretion)</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. A merchant left his satchel at the bar and has since vanished — dangerous men are asking questions.\n2. Someone is poisoning the town well; Quilby noticed a pattern in which regulars are falling ill.\n3. A beloved regular hasn't been in for two weeks — Quilby offers 20 gp for information.\n4. The Thieves' Guild doubled their protection fee — Quilby needs the party to negotiate or solve the problem.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. Quilby is mid-argument with a dwarf over a tab when the party enters.\n2. Quilby hires the party to recover a stolen cask of vintage wine — it's actually a smuggling container.\n3. Quilby is accused of poisoning a noble guest — his past makes him look guilty, but he's being framed.\n4. A hooded figure slides a letter under the door at night — Quilby frantically signals the party to intercept them.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
